title: Whirlpool Refrigerator freezer works but not fridge

full_content.content: Whirlpool Refrigerator freezer works but not fridge
Common reasons your Whirlpool Refrigerator freezer works but not fridge
The most common reasons your Whirlpool refrigerator freezer works but not the fridge are a broken air damper, a failed thermistor, or a malfunctioning PCB.
We can help! Our service technicians have repaired over 15,000 Whirlpool refrigerators. We can fix yours no matter where you bought it.
Most common repairs needed to fix a Whirlpool refrigerator

When you find your refrigerator too cold or not cold enough, a broken air damper could be allowing either too much or too little cold air into the refrigerator from the freezer. The air damper channels and controls the cold airflow from the freezer compartment into the refrigerator compartment to cool the refrigerator. The air damper is controlled by a dial in some refrigerators, and by the thermistor and electronic control board in other fridge models. If you feel excessive cold air in the refrigerator, or if the fresh-food compartment isn't cold enough, but the freezer is working okay, you'll likely need to have a Sears Home Services technician diagnose the problem and replace the air damper.
How to replace the air damper in a refrigerator

In refrigerator models that use an electronic control board to regulate temperatures, the thermistor is responsible for sensing internal temperatures. It then sends the temperature signal to the electronic control board. The electronic control turns the compressor on and off to regulate temperatures based on the thermistor temperature signal. An errant temperature signal can prevent the control board from regulating refrigerator and freezer temperature accurately.
How to replace a refrigerator thermistor

A defective printed circuit board (PCB) can lead to various failures in a refrigerator, including a lack of power, lack of cooling, and water leaks. The PCB controls communication and power between various components of a refrigerator that control temperature regulation, fan operation, the defrost cycle, icemaker functions, and dispenser functions. If the PCB fails, any or all of these components may stop working. Because so many components can be impacted, Sears Home Services professionals should conduct diagnostic tests on the board to confirm if replacement is necessary.

When the freezer works but the refrigerator section isn’t cooling, an airflow problem is likely causing the failure.

The owner’s manual typically show you where those supply and return vents are in your fridge.

The air damper controls airflow from the freezer to the refrigerator to help control the proper refrigerator temperature at around 37 degrees.
When the air damper gets stuck in the closed position, the refrigerator section won’t get any cooling air from the freezer.

However, there are many potential causes, so a thorough diagnosis is key to fixing the problem. An accurate diagnosis is essential to understanding how much the repair will be.

full_content.content: Why is my Whirlpool refrigerator freezer working but the fridge isn’t cooling?
A blocked air vent, malfunctioning evaporator fan, or faulty air damper could prevent the fridge from cooling properly. Inspect these components for issues.
Could a blocked air vent prevent my Whirlpool refrigerator from cooling?
Yes, if the air vent is blocked, cold air won’t circulate into the fridge. Clearing the vent should restore cooling.
How can I fix my Whirlpool refrigerator if the fridge isn’t cooling but the freezer is?
Check the air vents, evaporator fan, and air damper for issues. Replacing any faulty parts should restore cooling in the fridge.
What should I do if my Whirlpool refrigerator still isn’t cooling after clearing the vent?
If the fridge continues to not cool, the control board or compressor may need professional inspection and repair.

full_content.content: How Does a Refrigerator Ice Maker Work?
Learn how a refrigerator ice maker works and how to keep it in top shape.

A compressor is a mechanical device that increases the pressure of a gas by reducing its volume, essential in various systems including refrigerators, air conditioners, and HVAC units for cooling and refrigeration processes.
A condenser is a component of HVAC and refrigeration systems, responsible for releasing absorbed heat from the refrigerant into the outside air or a water line, thus facilitating the cooling process.
What is a Dual Ice Maker?

A dual ice maker is a feature in some refrigerators that includes two separate ice makers: one in the fridge compartment and another in the freezer section. This setup doubles the appliance's ice-making capacity.

A French-door refrigerator features two doors that open side-by-side on the top section for the refrigerator compartment, with a bottom freezer drawer, combining style, efficiency, and easy access to both refrigerated and frozen goods.
